results.deck: Comic imprint created in 2013 by Titan Magazines
results.description:
Originally comics were printed under the Titan Magazines and trades under Titan Books. In 2013 Titan created the comics imprint to publish original creator-owned comics alongside new and classic graphic novels!

The imprint will launch in July 2013 with two creator-owned miniseries and four new collections, with a new series beginning each month afterwards:

  • Chronos Commandos: Dawn Patrol by writer/artist Stuart Jennett (Marvel UK)
  • Numbercruncher by X-Men: Legacy writer Si Spurrier and 2000AD artist P.J. Holden
  • Ring of Roses – collected in color for the first time, by writer Das Petrou and artist John Watkiss
  • Thrud The Barbarian by writer/artist Carl Critchlow (2000AD, Magic: The Gathering)
  • The First Kingdom by comic legend Jack Katz

The second wave will see three new series launching later in the year:

September

  • Gravestown by writer Roger Gibson and artist Vince Danks (Harker)
  • Surface Tension by writer/artist Jay Gunn

October

  • Death Sentence by writer Monty Nero and artist Mike Dowling (2000AD, Rex Royd)
